From: M4 SGLang patches
Subject: mlx_vlm fallback for VLM model types in MlxModelRunner._load_model

The MLX runner uses `mlx_lm.load()` which only supports text-only
architectures. VLM architectures (Idefics3/SmolVLM/Qwen2-VL/etc.) raise
`ValueError: Model type X not supported.` and bring the scheduler down.

This patch:

1. Falls back to `mlx_vlm.load()` when `mlx_lm.load()` raises
   "not supported".
2. Wraps the loaded VLM Model in `_TextOnlyVLMShim` so that the existing
   call sites (`self.model(input_ids, cache=cache)`, all 5 of them in
   prefill/extend/decode_batch) route to `vlm.language_model(...)` for
   text-only requests.
3. Unwraps `LanguageModelOutput` so SGLang's `logits[:, -1, :]` indexing
   keeps working.

**Verified:** smol-docling preset (`ds4sd/SmolDocling-256M-preview-mlx-bf16`)
boots cleanly through SGLang and answers text-only requests. Output is
docling-style nonsense ("0>0>500>500>") because SmolDocling is a
docling-only model — not a quality issue, just a model choice. A real
general VLM (Qwen2-VL, etc.) will produce sensible text output.

**Not yet supported:** image-bearing requests. Those still need
`pixel_values` plumbed from SGLang's image processor to the VLM's
`get_input_embeddings()`. That's a separate patch (008?). For now the
shim only handles text-only — same scope as the patch 002 multimodal
disable.

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/hardware_backend/mlx/model_runner.py b/python/sglang/srt/hardware_backend/mlx/model_runner.py
--- a/python/sglang/srt/hardware_backend/mlx/model_runner.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/hardware_backend/mlx/model_runner.py
@@ -158,18 +158,46 @@ class MlxModelRunner:
     def _load_model(self):
-        """Load model using mlx_lm."""
+        """Load model using mlx_lm; fall back to mlx_vlm for VLM architectures."""
         logger.info(f"Loading MLX model: {self.model_path}")
         start_time = time.time()

-        self.model, _ = mlx_lm_load(
-            self.model_path,
-            tokenizer_config={"trust_remote_code": self.trust_remote_code},
-        )
+        try:
+            self.model, _ = mlx_lm_load(
+                self.model_path,
+                tokenizer_config={"trust_remote_code": self.trust_remote_code},
+            )
+            self.is_vlm = False
+        except ValueError as e:
+            if "not supported" not in str(e):
+                raise
+            logger.warning(
+                f"mlx_lm cannot load {self.model_path} ({e}); "
+                f"falling back to mlx_vlm. VLM inference path through "
+                f"SGLang is text-only for now (no pixel_values plumbing)."
+            )
+            try:
+                from mlx_vlm import load as mlx_vlm_load
+            except ImportError:
+                raise RuntimeError(
+                    f"Model {self.model_path} requires mlx_vlm but it isn't "
+                    f"installed. Run `pip install mlx-vlm`."
+                ) from e
+            self.model, self.processor = mlx_vlm_load(self.model_path)
+            self.is_vlm = True
+            _vlm_model = self.model
+            class _TextOnlyVLMShim:
+                def __init__(self, vlm):
+                    self._vlm = vlm
+                def __call__(self, input_ids, cache=None, **kwargs):
+                    out = self._vlm.language_model(input_ids, cache=cache)
+                    return getattr(out, "logits", out)
+                def __getattr__(self, name):
+                    return getattr(self._vlm, name)
+            self.model = _TextOnlyVLMShim(_vlm_model)
+
         # Force-evaluate weights so mx.get_active_memory() reflects
         # actual usage before KV pool sizing.
         mx.eval(self.model.parameters())

         load_time = time.time() - start_time
-        logger.info(f"MLX model loaded in {load_time:.2f}s")
+        logger.info(
+            f"MLX model loaded in {load_time:.2f}s "
+            f"(vlm={getattr(self, 'is_vlm', False)})"
+        )
